Teaches the basic knowledge, skills, and attitude for owning and operating a pistol safely.

This course is at least 8-hours long and includes classroom and range time learning to shoot revolvers and semi-automatic pistols. Students learn NRA’s rules for safe gun handling; pistol parts and operation; ammunition; shooting fundamentals; range rules; shooting from the bench rest position, and two handed standing positions; cleaning the pistol; and continued opportunities for skill development. Students will receive the NRA Guide to the Basics of Pistol Shooting handbook, NRA Gun Safety Rules brochure, Winchester/NRA Marksmanship Qualification booklet, take a Basics of Pistol Shooting Student Examination, and course completion certificate. 
-Course fee: $100

NRA First Steps Pistol Orientation:
Firearm Instruction, Responsibility, and Safety Training — is the NRA’s response to the American public’s need for a firearm orientation program for new purchasers.

NRA FIRST Steps Pistol is designed to provide a hands-on introduction to the safe handling and proper orientation to one specific pistol action type for classes of four or fewer students. This course is at least three hours long and includes classroom and range time learning to shoot a specific pistol action type. Students will learn the NRA’s rules for safe gun handling; the particular pistol model parts and operation; ammunition; shooting fundamentals; cleaning the pistol; and continued opportunities for skill development. Students will receive the Basics of Pistol Shooting handbook, NRA Gun Safety Rules brochure, Winchester/NRA Marksmanship Qualification booklet, FIRST Steps Course completion certificate.
-Course fee: $90

El Paso County Concealed Carry Training:
Due to the recent change in training requirements for El Paso County I have developed a new classroom-only course to teach students the basics of pistol shooting, handgun safety, and concealed carry options. I have spoke with the El Paso County Sherriff's Office about what is required for training and also what kind of training credentials are required to obtain your Concealed Handgun Permit.
-Course fee: $75

If you have any questions or are interested in any of the above courses please send me an E-mail or give me a call at REDACTED. 

Thank you

title: For Sale:  Gunsmith Build -- Colt series MK IV series 80 upper on a size 70
postcontent: The slide is a Colt Officers ACP with a 3&1/2 inch barrel. Because the slide is so short there was no room for the bushing to go when the slide went back. Therefore a larger bushing was made that slips over the barrel lugs during recoil, and the barrel diameter was belled to match. Another reason is with the shorter slide and barrel, the barrel angle would be too steep for the slide to function properly during recoil. A straight barrel would wedge the slide back during recoil. The shape of the bell keeps the barrel angled properly for slide function, and then realigns the barrel to the slide as the slide closes; there is a considerable amount of torque in a barrel and this is more evident in a short barrel. This barrel is beautifully bright.
